---
import Chapter from '../../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Neighborhoods", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Lake Forest", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/lake-forest"}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Place", "name": "Lake Forest, Illinois", "url": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/lake-forest", "containedInPlace": {"@type": "Place", "name": "North Shore, Chicago, IL"}}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Lake Forest — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="Lake Forest village brief — estate-scale architecture by Howard Van Doren Shaw and David Adler, six distinct sub-markets, and the Lake Forest District 67/115 school anchor."
  path="/neighborhoods/lake-forest" current="/neighborhoods" palette="0.15"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "Snapshot"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Architecture"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.15">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Lake Forest &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Six villages inside <em>one</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Lake Forest is the only North Shore village that holds six distinct sub-markets &mdash; the storied East Lake Forest estates, the western parcels beyond Western Avenue, and four neighborhoods between. Each operates on its own logic, its own price ladder, its own architectural lineage. A village of <em>extraordinary</em> range, carried as one corridor.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">View the snapshot &darr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/intelligence#ch-02">Open live dashboard</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.40">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">Lake Forest Snapshot</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        A village of <em>estates</em>, ravines, and lake bluffs.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Lake Forest's median list price sits at $1.32M across the full village &mdash; a headline that conceals extraordinary internal range. Estate sales east of Sheridan routinely close north of $5M, while the western sub-markets transact in the $700K&ndash;$1.1M band. Days-on-market run a measured 34; a sale-to-list ratio of 98.4% reflects disciplined pricing rather than buyer urgency. The price-per-square-foot of $487 is the corridor's clearest signal of land value and lot scale.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Median Price</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$1.32M</span><span class="d">Village-wide list median</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">Days on Market</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">34 days</span><span class="d up">Measured pace, disciplined pricing</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">SP/OLP</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">98.4%</span><span class="d">Sale-to-list ratio</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">$/SqFt</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$487</span><span class="d up">Reflects lot scale &amp; provenance</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="market-blend" style="padding:16px 24px 56px;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;background:#0A1838;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:16px;padding:22px 22px 12px;box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35);">
    <div id="blendedMarket"></div>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.65">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Architecture &amp; Schools</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Estate-scale <em>vocabulary</em>, top-tier schools.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        The village's architectural DNA was written by <strong>Howard Van Doren Shaw, David Adler, and Stanley Anderson</strong> &mdash; whose commissions across the first three decades of the twentieth century established Lake Forest as one of the country's defining estate communities. East of Sheridan, the lots run to multiple acres, the houses to ten- and twelve-thousand square feet, and the building stock leans Georgian, Tudor, and English country revival. West of Western Avenue, the parcels are tighter, the housing newer, and the architectural register shifts toward classic American suburban and contemporary.
      </p>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Lake Forest's K&ndash;8 students attend <strong>Lake Forest District 67</strong>, feeding into <strong>Lake Forest High School (District 115)</strong> &mdash; consistently ranked among the strongest public school districts in Illinois. The district is one of the most cited reasons families relocate to the village from Chicago's North Side, and a measurable component of the price premium attached to homes inside the boundary.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Move in <em>Lake Forest</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. We'll walk through the sub-market that fits your brief, the live inventory inside it, and the next three to six months of likely activity. No pitch.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-block fade-up">
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Direct</div><div class="v"><a href="tel:+18478499828" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">(847) 849-9828</a></div></div>
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Email</div><div class="v"><a href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com</a></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">Schedule the Call &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/neighborhoods">Back to neighborhoods</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(lds[1])} />
  <script slot="scripts" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script slot="scripts" src="/brand/charts/d3-brand.js" is:inline></script>
</Chapter>
